https://riczaman.github.io/notes-repo/
https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/setup/changing-the-colors/
---
| Syntax                            | Purpose                             | Example                                                  |
| --------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `#` / `##` / `###`                | Headings (H1, H2, H3)               | `## Jenkins Notes`                                       |
| `-` or `*`                        | Bullet lists                        | `- Item 1`                                               |
| `1.`                              | Numbered list                       | `1. Step one`                                            |
| `` `inline code` ``               | Inline code snippet                 | `Use the command \`docker run\`\`                        |
| <pre>`bash<br>commands<br>`</pre> | Code block with syntax highlighting | <pre>`bash<br>docker pull jenkins/jenkins:lts<br>`</pre> |
| `---` or `***`                    | Horizontal rule (separator line)    | `---`                                                    |
| `![alt](path)`                    | Image embedding                     | `![Jenkins](images/jenkins.png)`                         |
| `[text](url)`                     | Hyperlink                           | `[Jenkins](https://jenkins.io)`                          |
| `> blockquote`                    | Blockquote (for quotes or notes)    | `> Note: Jenkins is great`                               |

!!! note "Formatting Examples"
    Here are different ways to format text with colors:
    
    - **Bold text** (dark/emphasized)
    - *Italic text* (subtle emphasis)
    - `Code text` (monospace, different background)
    - ==Highlighted text== (yellow highlight)
    - ~~Strikethrough text~~ (grayed out)
    - [Link text](https://example.com) (blue, clickable)

!!! tip "Color Options"
    - **Bold** = Darker, emphasized
    - *Italic* = Subtle emphasis  
    - `Code` = Monospace with background
    - ==Highlight== = Yellow background
    - ~~Strike~~ = Grayed out
    - [Links] = Blue, clickable